<br>
even if you open a trade window with a charmed mob... if he breaks charm before you hit trade he won't finish the quest.<br>
<br>
however, if you don't wanna wait that long, maybe you can coerce a high level shaman or mage to come and malo/mala him for you. between that and tash that's a TON of mr off, and you should be able to do it.<br>
<br>
when you port in using hammer, you are aggroed by one low level mob... just mez him and then invis up, and there are many ways out of the outpost from there. some swim outside the outpost, others run through it invis, I've found both to be perfectly safe.<br>
<br>
...and root is our best spell =) doesn't really work in tov though, no real point to it. I suppose it could work to some effect on baby mobs seen in the very first area of ntov, but they tend to break it (and similar spells, like charm) very fast due to high MR, so not really worth it. still, it's been a very trusty spell line, and I feel naked when it's not memmed. <p><br><br>
